<title>USA: Reed-Elsevier files $1.75 bln shelf.</title>
<headline>Reed-Elsevier files $1.75 bln shelf.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Reed-Elsevier Capital Inc filed Tuesday with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission a shelf offering for up to $1.75 billion in debt.</p>
<p>When combined with previous registrations, the total offering will be $2.05 billion, according to the filing.</p>
<p>Underwriters for the offering may include Lehman Brothers Inc., Deutsche Morgan Grenfell, Goldman Sachs &amp; Co. or UBS Securities LLC.</p>
<p>Proceeds from the sale will be used for general corporate purposes. The company is a unit of Reed International Plc and Elsevier NV.</p>
